With 22mm compression connections, the valve includes a bronze body, wedge, screwed bonnet, non-rising stem, wheel handle and forged brass compression nuts. A gate valve, also known as a sluice valve, opens by lifting a barrier out of the path of a fluid. Gate valves normally require minimal space along the pipe axis and offer minimal flow restriction when fully open. A multiturn valve, operation of a gate valve is carried out via a threaded stem, turning multiple times to change position.
